From 9c6cf7e3fc652facb969a195269c808952f837e3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sirius902 <10891979+Sirius902@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 16:48:03 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] feat: pass OSC 52 clipboard-read through to host terminal
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Forward `\x1b]52;<sel>;?...` queries from panes out to the host terminal
and route the terminal's reply back to the focused pane. This lets apps
inside zellij (e.g. remote nvim) use OSC 52 paste without zellij adding
a second permissions layer on top of the host terminal's own prompt.

Mirrors the existing OSC 99 desktop-notification plumbing. OSC 52 writes
(copy) are untouched — those already work via ClipboardProvider.

Refs zellij-org/zellij#2647

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
